physical_examinations.relevant_findings: The patient was a young woman of average build and height, appeared inattentive and perplexed, avoided eye contact. Clothes were unironed and shabby, hair uncombed. No abnormal movements were observed, but she was restless and fidgety, unable to maintain focus during the conversation. Mood reported as 'theek' (OK). Affect was anxious, and thought process was tangential, with notable content of jinn possession. Denied hallucinations during the interview. Insight into the illness was absent.
